OL,3,C'Her name was Bebe... she deserved to
OL,4,Clive': Bebe King's parents tell Inquiry
OL,6,F"She was cheeky in the best way, with
OL,7,Fa wicked sense of humour far beyond
OL,8,Fher years."
OL,10,FShe told the inquiry the family had a
OL,11,Fsaying, "Be more Bebe", established
OL,12,Flong before the attack, indicating
OL,13,F"how strong her spirit was", "even
OL,14,Fthen, we wanted to live like her".
OL,16,FRecalling the day of the attack,
OL,17,FLauren said "something that should
OL,18,Fhave been safe, innocent, and joyful
OL,19,Fwas allowed to become a place of
OL,20,Fdanger and horror".
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/11
